92. The praetorship was established in 366 ne. to relieve the consul from jurisdiction in civil suits. At first a single praetor was elected annually by the comitia centuriata. He was regarded as the colleague of the consuls and assumed their duties at home when they were in the field. His special duties, however, were those of a judicial magistrate, but in dispensing justice he was usually assisted by iudicer,l judges or jurors, selected originally from the senate.
